{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":746,"text":"Well, I'm an ocean chemist."},{"time":2223,"text":"I look at the chemistry\nof the ocean today."},{"time":4366,"text":"I look at the chemistry\nof the ocean in the past."},{"time":7390,"text":"The way I look back in the past"},{"time":9478,"text":"is by using the fossilized remains\nof deepwater corals."},{"time":12653,"text":"You can see an image of one\nof these corals behind me."},{"time":15319,"text":"It was collected from close to Antarctica,\nthousands of meters below the sea,"},{"time":19769,"text":"so, very different\nthan the kinds of corals"},{"time":21881,"text":"you may have been lucky enough to see\nif you've had a tropical holiday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25692,"text":"So I'm hoping that this talk will give you"},{"time":27772,"text":"a four-dimensional view of the ocean."},{"time":29589,"text":"Two dimensions, such as this\nbeautiful two-dimensional image"},{"time":33486,"text":"of the sea surface temperature."},{"time":35104,"text":"This was taken using satellite,\nso it's got tremendous spatial resolution."},{"time":39898,"text":"The overall features are extremely\neasy to understand."},{"time":42788,"text":"The equatorial regions are warm\nbecause there's more sunlight."},{"time":46476,"text":"The polar regions are cold\nbecause there's less sunlight."},{"time":49186,"text":"And that allows big icecaps\nto build up on Antarctica"},{"time":52131,"text":"and up in the Northern Hemisphere."},{"time":54299,"text":"If you plunge deep into the sea,\nor even put your toes in the sea,"},{"time":57741,"text":"you know it gets colder as you go down,"},{"time":59708,"text":"and that's mostly because the deep waters\nthat fill the abyss of the ocean"},{"time":63711,"text":"come from the cold polar regions\nwhere the waters are dense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67845,"text":"If we travel back in time\n20,000 years ago,"},{"time":70975,"text":"the earth looked very much different."},{"time":72859,"text":"And I've just given you a cartoon version\nof one of the major differences"},{"time":76350,"text":"you would have seen\nif you went back that long."},{"time":78629,"text":"The icecaps were much bigger."},{"time":80335,"text":"They covered lots of the continent,\nand they extended out over the ocean."},{"time":83986,"text":"Sea level was 120 meters lower."},{"time":86503,"text":"Carbon dioxide [levels] were very\nmuch lower than they are today."},{"time":90071,"text":"So the earth was probably about three\nto five degrees colder overall,"},{"time":93739,"text":"and much, much colder\nin the polar regions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97908,"text":"What I'm trying to understand,"},{"time":99386,"text":"and what other colleagues of mine\nare trying to understand,"},{"time":102212,"text":"is how we moved from that\ncold climate condition"},{"time":104695,"text":"to the warm climate condition\nthat we enjoy today."},{"time":107615,"text":"We know from ice core research"},{"time":109698,"text":"that the transition from these\ncold conditions to warm conditions"},{"time":112802,"text":"wasn't smooth, as you might predict\nfrom the slow increase in solar radiation."},{"time":118153,"text":"And we know this from ice cores,\nbecause if you drill down into ice,"},{"time":121408,"text":"you find annual bands of ice,\nand you can see this in the iceberg."},{"time":124703,"text":"You can see those blue-white layers."},{"time":126718,"text":"Gases are trapped in the ice cores,\nso we can measure CO2 --"},{"time":130368,"text":"that's why we know CO2\nwas lower in the past --"},{"time":132757,"text":"and the chemistry of the ice\nalso tells us about temperature"},{"time":135774,"text":"in the polar regions."},{"time":137273,"text":"And if you move in time\nfrom 20,000 years ago to the modern day,"},{"time":140976,"text":"you see that temperature increased."},{"time":142809,"text":"It didn't increase smoothly."},{"time":144458,"text":"Sometimes it increased very rapidly,"},{"time":146260,"text":"then there was a plateau,"},{"time":147528,"text":"then it increased rapidly."},{"time":148817,"text":"It was different in the two polar regions,"},{"time":150865,"text":"and CO2 also increased in jumps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154808,"text":"So we're pretty sure the ocean\nhas a lot to do with this."},{"time":157878,"text":"The ocean stores huge amounts of carbon,"},{"time":160268,"text":"about 60 times more\nthan is in the atmosphere."},{"time":162846,"text":"It also acts to transport heat\nacross the equator,"},{"time":166072,"text":"and the ocean is full of nutrients\nand it controls primary productivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170142,"text":"So if we want to find out\nwhat's going on down in the deep sea,"},{"time":173150,"text":"we really need to get down there,"},{"time":174767,"text":"see what's there"},{"time":175957,"text":"and start to explore."},{"time":177385,"text":"This is some spectacular footage\ncoming from a seamount"},{"time":180416,"text":"about a kilometer deep\nin international waters"},{"time":182629,"text":"in the equatorial Atlantic, far from land."},{"time":185633,"text":"You're amongst the first people\nto see this bit of the seafloor,"},{"time":188706,"text":"along with my research team."},{"time":191340,"text":"You're probably seeing new species."},{"time":193108,"text":"We don't know."},{"time":194284,"text":"You'd have to collect the samples\nand do some very intense taxonomy."},{"time":197968,"text":"You can see beautiful bubblegum corals."},{"time":199885,"text":"There are brittle stars\ngrowing on these corals."},{"time":202163,"text":"Those are things that look\nlike tentacles coming out of corals."},{"time":205243,"text":"There are corals made of different forms\nof calcium carbonate"},{"time":208139,"text":"growing off the basalt of this\nmassive undersea mountain,"},{"time":211539,"text":"and the dark sort of stuff,\nthose are fossilized corals,"},{"time":214927,"text":"and we're going to talk\na little more about those"},{"time":217262,"text":"as we travel back in time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219030,"text":"To do that, we need\nto charter a research boat."},{"time":221539,"text":"This is the James Cook,\nan ocean-class research vessel"},{"time":224603,"text":"moored up in Tenerife."},{"time":225897,"text":"Looks beautiful, right?"},{"time":227554,"text":"Great, if you're not a great mariner."},{"time":229702,"text":"Sometimes it looks\na little more like this."},{"time":232230,"text":"This is us trying to make sure\nthat we don't lose precious samples."},{"time":235453,"text":"Everyone's scurrying around,\nand I get terribly seasick,"},{"time":238294,"text":"so it's not always a lot of fun,\nbut overall it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241312,"text":"So we've got to become\na really good mapper to do this."},{"time":243922,"text":"You don't see that kind of spectacular\ncoral abundance everywhere."},{"time":247685,"text":"It is global and it is deep,"},{"time":250749,"text":"but we need to really find\nthe right places."},{"time":253087,"text":"We just saw a global map,\nand overlaid was our cruise passage"},{"time":256277,"text":"from last year."},{"time":257990,"text":"This was a seven-week cruise,"},{"time":259410,"text":"and this is us, having made our own maps"},{"time":261458,"text":"of about 75,000 square kilometers\nof the seafloor in seven weeks,"},{"time":265553,"text":"but that's only a tiny fraction\nof the seafloor."},{"time":268099,"text":"We're traveling from west to east,"},{"time":269892,"text":"over part of the ocean that would\nlook featureless on a big-scale map,"},{"time":273416,"text":"but actually some of these mountains\nare as big as Everest."},{"time":276697,"text":"So with the maps that we make on board,"},{"time":278650,"text":"we get about 100-meter resolution,"},{"time":280666,"text":"enough to pick out areas\nto deploy our equipment,"},{"time":283579,"text":"but not enough to see very much."},{"time":285517,"text":"To do that, we need to fly\nremotely-operated vehicles"},{"time":288263,"text":"about five meters off the seafloor."},{"time":290501,"text":"And if we do that, we can get maps\nthat are one-meter resolution"},{"time":293740,"text":"down thousands of meters."},{"time":295858,"text":"Here is a remotely-operated vehicle,"},{"time":297699,"text":"a research-grade vehicle."},{"time":300034,"text":"You can see an array\nof big lights on the top."},{"time":302540,"text":"There are high-definition cameras,\nmanipulator arms,"},{"time":305619,"text":"and lots of little boxes and things\nto put your samples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309087,"text":"Here we are on our first dive\nof this particular cruise,"},{"time":312829,"text":"plunging down into the ocean."},{"time":314559,"text":"We go pretty fast to make sure\nthe remotely operated vehicles"},{"time":317456,"text":"are not affected by any other ships."},{"time":319203,"text":"And we go down,"},{"time":320425,"text":"and these are the kinds of things you see."},{"time":322623,"text":"These are deep sea sponges, meter scale."},{"time":326817,"text":"This is a swimming holothurian --\nit's a small sea slug, basically."},{"time":331089,"text":"This is slowed down."},{"time":332300,"text":"Most of the footage I'm showing\nyou is speeded up,"},{"time":334713,"text":"because all of this takes a lot of time."},{"time":337474,"text":"This is a beautiful holothurian as well."},{"time":340897,"text":"And this animal you're going to see\ncoming up was a big surprise."},{"time":343993,"text":"I've never seen anything like this\nand it took us all a bit surprised."},{"time":347429,"text":"This was after about 15 hours of work\nand we were all a bit trigger-happy,"},{"time":351041,"text":"and suddenly this giant\nsea monster started rolling past."},{"time":353802,"text":"It's called a pyrosome\nor colonial tunicate, if you like."},{"time":356932,"text":"This wasn't what we were looking for."},{"time":358743,"text":"We were looking for corals,\ndeep sea corals."},{"time":362194,"text":"You're going to see a picture\nof one in a moment."},{"time":364516,"text":"It's small, about five centimeters high."},{"time":367175,"text":"It's made of calcium carbonate,\nso you can see its tentacles there,"},{"time":370517,"text":"moving in the ocean currents."},{"time":373180,"text":"An organism like this probably lives\nfor about a hundred years."},{"time":376315,"text":"And as it grows, it takes in\nchemicals from the ocean."},{"time":379879,"text":"And the chemicals,\nor the amount of chemicals,"},{"time":382109,"text":"depends on the temperature;\nit depends on the pH,"},{"time":384807,"text":"it depends on the nutrients."},{"time":386377,"text":"And if we can understand how\nthese chemicals get into the skeleton,"},{"time":389635,"text":"we can then go back,\ncollect fossil specimens,"},{"time":392157,"text":"and reconstruct what the ocean\nused to look like in the past."},{"time":395325,"text":"And here you can see us collecting\nthat coral with a vacuum system,"},{"time":398785,"text":"and we put it into a sampling container."},{"time":401410,"text":"We can do this very\ncarefully, I should add."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403493,"text":"Some of these organisms live even longer."},{"time":405902,"text":"This is a black coral called Leiopathes,\nan image taken by my colleague,"},{"time":409328,"text":"Brendan Roark, about 500\nmeters below Hawaii."},{"time":412614,"text":"Four thousand years is a long time."},{"time":414962,"text":"If you take a branch from one\nof these corals and polish it up,"},{"time":418121,"text":"this is about 100 microns across."},{"time":420763,"text":"And Brendan took some analyses\nacross this coral --"},{"time":423278,"text":"you can see the marks --"},{"time":425108,"text":"and he's been able to show\nthat these are actual annual bands,"},{"time":428091,"text":"so even at 500 meters deep in the ocean,"},{"time":430028,"text":"corals can record seasonal changes,"},{"time":432820,"text":"which is pretty spectacular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434576,"text":"But 4,000 years is not enough to get\nus back to our last glacial maximum."},{"time":438398,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":439580,"text":"We go in for these fossil specimens."},{"time":442180,"text":"This is what makes me really unpopular\nwith my research team."},{"time":445135,"text":"So going along,"},{"time":446309,"text":"there's giant sharks everywhere,"},{"time":447951,"text":"there are pyrosomes,\nthere are swimming holothurians,"},{"time":450473,"text":"there's giant sponges,"},{"time":451768,"text":"but I make everyone go down\nto these dead fossil areas"},{"time":454387,"text":"and spend ages kind of shoveling\naround on the seafloor."},{"time":457967,"text":"And we pick up all these corals,\nbring them back, we sort them out."},{"time":461356,"text":"But each one of these is a different age,"},{"time":463675,"text":"and if we can find out how old they are"},{"time":465600,"text":"and then we can measure\nthose chemical signals,"},{"time":468136,"text":"this helps us to find out"},{"time":469582,"text":"what's been going on\nin the ocean in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472558,"text":"So on the left-hand image here,"},{"time":474286,"text":"I've taken a slice through a coral,\npolished it very carefully"},{"time":477342,"text":"and taken an optical image."},{"time":479336,"text":"On the right-hand side,"},{"time":480512,"text":"we've taken that same piece of coral,\nput it in a nuclear reactor,"},{"time":483636,"text":"induced fission,"},{"time":484812,"text":"and every time there's some decay,"},{"time":486467,"text":"you can see that marked out in the coral,"},{"time":488473,"text":"so we can see the uranium distribution."},{"time":490386,"text":"Why are we doing this?"},{"time":491561,"text":"Uranium is a very poorly regarded element,"},{"time":493872,"text":"but I love it."},{"time":495055,"text":"The decay helps us find out\nabout the rates and dates"},{"time":498291,"text":"of what's going on in the ocean."},{"time":499854,"text":"And if you remember from the beginning,"},{"time":501776,"text":"that's what we want to get at\nwhen we're thinking about climate."},{"time":504813,"text":"So we use a laser to analyze uranium"},{"time":506588,"text":"and one of its daughter products,\nthorium, in these corals,"},{"time":509397,"text":"and that tells us exactly\nhow old the fossils are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512742,"text":"This beautiful animation\nof the Southern Ocean"},{"time":514958,"text":"I'm just going to use illustrate\nhow we're using these corals"},{"time":518117,"text":"to get at some of the ancient\nocean feedbacks."},{"time":522212,"text":"You can see the density\nof the surface water"},{"time":524662,"text":"in this animation by Ryan Abernathey."},{"time":527481,"text":"It's just one year of data,"},{"time":529542,"text":"but you can see how dynamic\nthe Southern Ocean is."},{"time":532500,"text":"The intense mixing,\nparticularly the Drake Passage,"},{"time":535931,"text":"which is shown by the box,"},{"time":538392,"text":"is really one of the strongest\ncurrents in the world"},{"time":541028,"text":"coming through here,\nflowing from west to east."},{"time":543259,"text":"It's very turbulently mixed,"},{"time":544632,"text":"because it's moving over those\ngreat big undersea mountains,"},{"time":547528,"text":"and this allows CO2 and heat to exchange\nwith the atmosphere in and out."},{"time":552033,"text":"And essentially, the oceans are breathing\nthrough the Southern Ocean."},{"time":556865,"text":"We've collected corals from back and forth\nacross this Antarctic passage,"},{"time":562353,"text":"and we've found quite a surprising thing\nfrom my uranium dating:"},{"time":565404,"text":"the corals migrated from south to north"},{"time":567931,"text":"during this transition from the glacial\nto the interglacial."},{"time":571084,"text":"We don't really know why,"},{"time":572315,"text":"but we think it's something\nto do with the food source"},{"time":574888,"text":"and maybe the oxygen in the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577718,"text":"So here we are."},{"time":578897,"text":"I'm going to illustrate what I think\nwe've found about climate"},{"time":581969,"text":"from those corals in the Southern Ocean."},{"time":583953,"text":"We went up and down sea mountains.\nWe collected little fossil corals."},{"time":587252,"text":"This is my illustration of that."},{"time":588802,"text":"We think back in the glacial,"},{"time":590231,"text":"from the analysis\nwe've made in the corals,"},{"time":592278,"text":"that the deep part of the Southern Ocean\nwas very rich in carbon,"},{"time":595388,"text":"and there was a low-density\nlayer sitting on top."},{"time":598101,"text":"That stops carbon dioxide\ncoming out of the ocean."},{"time":601752,"text":"We then found corals\nthat are of an intermediate age,"},{"time":604368,"text":"and they show us that the ocean mixed\npartway through that climate transition."},{"time":608972,"text":"That allows carbon to come\nout of the deep ocean."},{"time":612154,"text":"And then if we analyze corals\ncloser to the modern day,"},{"time":615277,"text":"or indeed if we go down there today anyway"},{"time":617555,"text":"and measure the chemistry of the corals,"},{"time":619785,"text":"we see that we move to a position\nwhere carbon can exchange in and out."},{"time":623803,"text":"So this is the way\nwe can use fossil corals"},{"time":625901,"text":"to help us learn about the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629827,"text":"So I want to leave you\nwith this last slide."},{"time":631985,"text":"It's just a still taken out of that first\npiece of footage that I showed you."},{"time":635932,"text":"This is a spectacular coral garden."},{"time":638068,"text":"We didn't even expect\nto find things this beautiful."},{"time":640650,"text":"It's thousands of meters deep."},{"time":642558,"text":"There are new species."},{"time":644416,"text":"It's just a beautiful place."},{"time":646339,"text":"There are fossils in amongst,"},{"time":647744,"text":"and now I've trained you\nto appreciate the fossil corals"},{"time":650459,"text":"that are down there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651698,"text":"So next time you're lucky enough\nto fly over the ocean"},{"time":654588,"text":"or sail over the ocean,"},{"time":656021,"text":"just think -- there are massive\nsea mountains down there"},{"time":658712,"text":"that nobody's ever seen before,"},{"time":660603,"text":"and there are beautiful corals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662244,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663419,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}